Privacy Policy for Status Saver Pro

Last updated: March 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how Status Saver Pro ("the App", "we", "us", or
"our") handles information when you use our Android application. We are committed
to protecting your privacy. Please read this policy carefully.

─────────────────────────────────────
1. INFORMATION WE DO NOT COLLECT
─────────────────────────────────────

Status Saver Pro does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personally
identifiable information (PII). Specifically:

  • We do not require you to create an account or log in.
  • We do not collect your name, email address, phone number, or any personal
    identifier.
  • We do not track your location.
  • We do not access your contacts list.
  • We do not read, transmit, or store the content of your WhatsApp messages
    beyond displaying them temporarily on your device screen.
  • We do not upload any files, photos, or videos to any remote server.
  • We do not sell, rent, or share any data with third parties.

─────────────────────────────────────
2. INFORMATION PROCESSED LOCALLY ON YOUR DEVICE
─────────────────────────────────────

The App processes the following data entirely on your device and never sends
it anywhere:

  a) WhatsApp Status Media
     The App reads media files (images, videos, GIFs) from WhatsApp's and
     WhatsApp Business's status directories on your device's local storage.
     These files are displayed within the App and, if you choose, saved to
     your device gallery. No file is sent to any server.

  b) WhatsApp Notification Data (Deleted Messages Feature)
     If you grant Notification Listener permission, the App reads the text
     and sender name from incoming WhatsApp and WhatsApp Business
     notifications. This data is stored in an encrypted local database on
     your device only. It is never transmitted off your device. You can
     delete this data at any time from within the App (Deleted tab →
     Clear All).

  c) App Preferences
     The App saves your in-app settings (e.g., auto-save toggle, dark mode
     preference, folder access permissions) locally using Android's
     SharedPreferences. This data is not accessible to us or any third party.

─────────────────────────────────────
3. PERMISSIONS WE REQUEST AND WHY
─────────────────────────────────────

The App requests the following Android permissions:

  • READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE / READ_MEDIA_IMAGES / READ_MEDIA_VIDEO
    → Required to read and display WhatsApp status files on your device.

  • WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE / MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
    → Required to save status photos and videos to your gallery.

  • BIND_NOTIFICATION_LISTENER_SERVICE / POST_NOTIFICATIONS
    → Required for the optional Deleted Messages feature. The App uses this
      to read the text of WhatsApp notifications before they disappear.
      This permission is optional — the App works without it; only the
      Deleted Messages tab requires it. You can revoke this permission
      at any time in Android Settings → Notification Access.

  • FOREGROUND_SERVICE / FOREGROUND_SERVICE_DATA_SYNC
    → Required to run the background file-watching service that detects
      new WhatsApp statuses in real time. A persistent notification is
      shown while this service is active, as required by Android.

  • RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED
    → Required to restart the background service automatically when your
      device reboots, so status monitoring continues without manual action.

  • INTERNET / ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE
    → Required to display ads if ad services are integrated in a future
      version. Currently, the App makes no network requests for user data.

  • VIBRATE
    → Used to provide haptic feedback when saving a file.

─────────────────────────────────────
4. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
─────────────────────────────────────

The current version of Status Saver Pro does not integrate any third-party
analytics, advertising, or crash-reporting SDKs. If this changes in a future
version, this policy will be updated accordingly and users will be notified
via an app update.

─────────────────────────────────────
5. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
─────────────────────────────────────

Status Saver Pro is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not
knowingly collect any personal information from children. If you believe a
child has provided personal information through the App, please contact us
and we will take appropriate action.

─────────────────────────────────────
6. DATA SECURITY
─────────────────────────────────────

Since we do not collect or transmit any user data, the risk of a data breach
affecting our users is minimal. All data processed by the App (notification
history, preferences) is stored locally on your device and protected by your
device's own security mechanisms (screen lock, encryption).

─────────────────────────────────────
7. DATA RETENTION AND DELETION
─────────────────────────────────────

  • Saved status files: Stored in your device gallery under the folder
    "StatusSaverPro" until you delete them manually.
  • Deleted message records: Stored locally on your device until you tap
    "Clear All" in the Deleted tab, or until you uninstall the App.
  • App preferences: Cleared automatically when you uninstall the App.

We have no access to any of this data and cannot delete it on your behalf.
You are in full control.

─────────────────────────────────────
8. YOUR RIGHTS
─────────────────────────────────────

Since all data is stored locally on your device and we collect nothing, you
have full control at all times:

  • Access: View your saved statuses and deleted messages in the App.
  • Delete: Use the in-app delete functions or uninstall the App.
  • Revoke permissions: Go to Android Settings → Apps → Status Saver Pro
    → Permissions and revoke any permission at any time.

─────────────────────────────────────
9. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
─────────────────────────────────────

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be
posted at the same URL and the "Last updated" date at the top will be revised.
Continued use of the App after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance
of the updated policy.

